---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Living in New Braunfels, TX | What to Expect | Cody Posey Real Estate"
  description="What daily life in New Braunfels is really like — commutes, culture, growth, weather, and who this city is best for."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="nb-hero">
      <div class="nb-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="nb-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/new-braunfels/">New Braunfels</a> <span>/</span> <span>Living Here</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Living in <span style="color:#FF1616;">New Braunfels</span></h1>
        <p>What daily life actually looks like — beyond the brochure</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Daily Life -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>What to <span class="accent">Expect</span></h2>
        <p class="nb-page-intro">New Braunfels is growing fast, but it still holds onto the things that made people want to live here in the first place. It's not a suburb — it's its own city with its own identity. Here's an honest look at what living here is actually like.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Culture & Lifestyle -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Culture & <span class="accent">Lifestyle</span></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="living__grid">
          <div class="living__card">
            <h3>Gruene & the River</h3>
            <p>Gruene Historic District is the cultural anchor — live music at Gruene Hall, local shops, wine tasting, and the Guadalupe River. Tubing season brings crowds in summer, but locals learn to navigate around it. The river culture is a real part of daily life here, not just a tourist attraction.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__card">
            <h3>Downtown & Local Scene</h3>
            <p>Downtown New Braunfels has its own personality — German bakeries, local restaurants, the Comal River, and Landa Park. First Fridays bring people out, and the farmers market is a weekend staple. It feels like a real town, not a manufactured one.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__card">
            <h3>Outdoor Living</h3>
            <p>Between the rivers, Natural Bridge Caverns, Canyon Lake, and the Hill Country trails, outdoor activities are a daily option — not a weekend trip. The climate supports year-round outdoor living, though summers are hot and dry (expect 95-100+ from June through September).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__card">
            <h3>Community Events</h3>
            <p>Wurstfest in the fall, Wassailfest in December, and a steady calendar of local events keep the community connected. The German heritage is still visible in the architecture, food, and festivals — it's part of the city's character.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Practical Realities -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Practical <span class="accent">Realities</span></h2>
          <p>The things you should know before committing</p>
        </div>
        <div class="living__realities">
          <div class="living__reality">
            <h3>Commute</h3>
            <p>San Antonio is roughly 30-40 minutes south on I-35 (outside rush hour). Austin is 45-60 minutes north. Rush hour adds time, and I-35 construction is a constant. Many residents work remotely or have flexible schedules. If you're commuting daily to downtown Austin, factor in the drive honestly.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__reality">
            <h3>Growth & Traffic</h3>
            <p>New Braunfels is one of the fastest-growing cities in Texas. That means new retail, restaurants, and amenities are coming — but it also means construction, traffic on I-35 and FM 306, and neighborhoods that are still being built out. The city is actively investing in infrastructure, but growth is outpacing it in some areas.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__reality">
            <h3>Weather</h3>
            <p>Mild winters are a real draw. Spring and fall are excellent. Summers are hot — consistently in the mid-to-upper 90s from June through September. If you're coming from a cooler climate, be prepared. Air conditioning is a requirement, not a luxury.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__reality">
            <h3>Tourism Seasons</h3>
            <p>Summer brings tubing crowds to the rivers and visitors to Schlitterbahn and Gruene. Weekends from May to September can feel busy in certain areas. Locals learn the patterns and adjust. Outside of peak season, the city settles into a quieter rhythm.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Best Fit -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Who <span class="accent">Fits Here</span></h2>
          <p>New Braunfels works well for certain lifestyles — here's how different buyers tend to experience it</p>
        </div>
        <div class="living__fit-grid">
          <div class="living__fit">
            <h3>Families</h3>
            <p>Strong school districts, safe neighborhoods, parks, rivers, and a community-oriented culture make this a top choice for families. Master-planned communities offer pools, playgrounds, and proximity to schools.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__fit">
            <h3>Commuters</h3>
            <p>If you work in San Antonio, the commute is manageable. Austin commuters should consider the drive carefully. The south side of the city and I-35 corridor provide the quickest highway access for daily commutes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__fit">
            <h3>Retirees</h3>
            <p>No state income tax, lower cost of living than major metros, healthcare access in San Antonio, and a pace of life that slows down without feeling isolated. Several communities cater specifically to 55+ buyers.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__fit">
            <h3>Remote Workers</h3>
            <p>If you work from home, New Braunfels is hard to beat. Hill Country views, lower housing costs, strong internet infrastructure in newer communities, and proximity to two airports when you need to travel.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Not Sure Which Area <span class="accent">Fits You</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">Tell me about your lifestyle, commute, and priorities — I'll help you narrow down the neighborhoods and areas that make the most sense.</p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a href="/new-braunfels/neighborhoods/" class="btn btn-primary">Explore Neighborhoods</a>
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Talk Through Areas That Fit</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/guadalupe-river.png" />

  <ContactForm context="I'd like to discuss which areas fit my lifestyle..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .nb-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/comal-river.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .nb-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .nb-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .nb-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .nb-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .nb-page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  /* Grid Cards */
  .living__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .living__card {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .living__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .living__card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Realities */
  .living__realities {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .living__reality {
    border-left: 3px solid #FF1616;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    background: #fafafa;
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  }

  .living__reality h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .living__reality p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Fit Grid */
  .living__fit-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .living__fit {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .living__fit h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .living__fit p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .living__grid,
    .living__fit-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
